Sacem
in a nutshell

   Since 1851

   SACEM (Society of Authors, Composers and Publishers of Music) is a
   non-profit non-trading entity owned and managed by its members
   according to the business model of a cooperative.

   To guarantee authors’ intellectual property rights over their works,
   SACEM collects and distributes royalties, thereby playing a crucial
   economic role to preserve musical creation.

   Learn more about SACEM

Sacem:
three basic values

   SACEM offers the same services to every one of its members, without
   distinction:

collecting
&AMP; distributing

   royalties

promoting
&AMP; supporting

   creators

defending
&AMP; protecting

   our members and authors’ rights

   Understand our role

Our
members and our clients

More than 169,400 creators and publishers,

   in France and worldwide, trust SACEM to protect their works and to
   support them in their projects.

   Learn about members’ services

More than 506,000 clients

   worldwide use more than 140 million works.

   Learn about clients’ benefits

SACEM
INNOVATION

   SACEM supports creation actively and sustainably. With our experience
   and unequalled expertise in collective management, we invest in
   projects and partnerships to develop innovative solutions and services.

   Open Innovation at SACEM means:

   Innovative applications to identify how our repertoire is used, support
   and facilitate clients’ procedures, distribute royalties accurately and
   improve services to our members.

   Partnerships with international technology groups, authors’ societies,
   start-ups, research centres and institutions of higher learning
   (Grandes Écoles).

   DISCOVER THE INNOVATIONS

